MIS Service Billing and Central System -- PREDAILY (PREDLY.INF)   01/28/85

General information - Customer/User validation and pricing information
must be moved daily from the validations host to be current with the 
service data gathered from the hosts.  The data is collected for 
Tymcom and Tymnet customers.  This data is updated into MAGNUM relations.
This information is used by each of the separate daily processes for the 
three Tymcom, one Tymnet, and one Tymuse services.  The processing directory
is UAS:38 and the approximate run time is two (2) hours.

Step 1.   Set the Billing dates for update of relation INV.TRK.DATES.
          The Xexec file TRKDAT.DAT is modified by the EDP operators.
          Magnum program is SET.BILLING.DATES, Schema is CAIS.

Step 2.   Copy the Validation data base from CUD10:38 to the Central
          System data base in UAS:38.  This is done by the Xexec COPY command.

          CUSTDB.DMS
          ADDRDB.DMS
          USERDB.DMS
          USYSDB.DMS
          VALDAT.DMS
          TYMCUS.DMS
          TYMUSR.DMS
          TUSRDB.DMS
          TUPRDC.DAT       to the directory TYMUSEA:38

Step 3.   Convert the Validation X22 files into Xexec files.
          1022 program CNVERT in directory UAS:38.

          Input file                         Output file
          ==========                         ===========
          CUSTDB.DMS                         CUSTDB.DMI
          USERDB.DMS                         USERDB.DMI
          USYSDB.DMS                         USYSDB.DMI
          VALDAT.DMS                         VALDAT.DMI
          ADDRDB.DMS                         ADDRDB.DMI
          CUSTDB.DMS  (TYMNET customers)     TCUSDB.DMI
          TUSRDB.DMS  (TYMNET customers)     TUSRDB.DMI
          ADDRDB.DMS  (TYMNET customers)     TADRDB.DMI
          TYMCUS.DMS  (TYMUSE customers)     TYMCUS.DMI  in TYMUSEA:38
          TYMUSR.DMS  (TYMUSE customers)     TYMUSR.DMI  in TYMUSEA:38

Step 4.   Backup the current MAGNUM relations in Schema CAIS.

          CUSTOMER, CUS.ADDR, UUN.USR.NAM, USER.ACTG.SYS, VAL

Step 5.   Run Magnum program CUS.REL.UPD to update the following relations:

          UUN.USR.NAM     from input file     USERDB.DMI
          USER.ACTG.SYS   from input file     USYSDB.DMI
          VAL             from input file     VALDAT.DMI
          CUSTOMER        from input file     CUSTDB.DMI
          CUS.ADDR        from input file     ADDRDB.DMI

Step 6.   Run MAGNUM program CUS.DIS.ACC.CHK to check the Customer
          District for accuracy.

